benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Add tags to account

covered: Valid Payload scenarios: tests for successful creation with 1 or more tag definitions (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05).

Input validation and malformed payload: tests for empty body (TC07), non-array body (TC08), invalid tag definition IDs (TC09), non-existent tag definitions (TC10), missing required header (TC11), missing accountId (TC12), invalid accountId format (TC13), non-existent account (TC14), extra unexpected fields (TC17).
Authorization and header validation: tests for missing authentication token (TC15) and header sanitization (TC22).
Account and tag definition validation: tests for missing accountId, invalid accountId, non-existent accounts/definitions (TC10-TC14).
Duplicates and existing state: tests for duplicates in request (TC19) and existing tags handling (TC05).
Boundary and performance: large payload (TC18), slow response (TC20), concurrent requests (TC21).
Query parameters ignored: test ensures limit/offset/sort are ignored (TC06).
Error handling: system error/dependency failure (TC16) and various invalid body cases (TC07, TC08, TC17), and service unavailability (TC16).
Regression and compatibility: special character ID regression (TC23) and API version backward compatibility (TC24).
gaps: Pagination actual results: no dedicated tests for validating paginated responses or exact paging logic beyond ignoring query params (TC06 only).
Caching headers: no tests validating ETag or Cache-Control presence in 200 responses.
Rate limiting/throttling: no tests simulating bursts or throttling behavior.
Internal server error coverage: only 503 is tested; no 500 Internal Server Error scenarios.
Forbidden/authorization scope: no tests for 403 when user lacks permission.
Additional validation scenarios: tests for mixed valid/invalid tag IDs in batch beyond format/ existence.
recommendations: Add tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to differentiate from 503 Service Unavailable.
Add tests for 403 Forbidden when user lacks required permissions.
Add tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) in 200 responses.
Add rate-limiting tests and concurrent stress scenarios with quantified time or request limits.
Add explicit pagination tests with varied page sizes and ensure correct items per page.
Ensure automated checks for idempotent behavior on repeated same payload, including duplicates across requests.
